data.description: Searching for a serene abode nestled among mature trees and meticulously landscaped yards? Welcome to 600 Bindon Lane, Simpsonville, situated in the charming Morning Mist Subdivision. This expansive home boasts a prime location on a picturesque corner lot, lining a tree-adorned street. Moreover, its proximity to the community pool and playground—directly across the street—is unbeatable. Take note: while the playground & pool are in clear view, it is convenience without overwhelming noise. Upon entering this 4-bedroom, 2.5-bath haven, you're greeted by a harmonious open floor plan, ideal for hosting and entertaining. The holiday season will truly shine in the kitchen, spacious enough to accommodate all the culinary enthusiasts in your family. Revel in the ample countertop space accentuated by a generously-sized island—perfect for gathering or lending a hand in meal prep. The sizable pantry is an added bonus, elevating this kitchen's appeal. Adjacent to it, the eating area provides beautiful views of the tree-lined backyard, infused with an abundance of natural light and is large enough for a regular sized table. Beyond the kitchen, the dining room stands ready to host holiday meals or intimate dinners. The adjoining family room exudes warmth, especially with the inviting fireplace to cozy up to during chilly evenings. Whether it's game nights, movie marathons, or quiet evenings, this space is versatile to fit all your needs. The adjoining living room could be closed off and used as an office or leave it as it sits and enjoy the additional space. There is a 1/2 bath on the first floor for your guests to use.  The service door from the garage to the interior makes it easy to bring in those groceries and deliver them right to the kitchen. As you venture upstairs, the bedrooms await. The owner's suite is a true retreat, offering ample space for your furnishings. Its en-suite bath is a testament to luxury. It has a double vanity, garden tub and separate shower with a great walk-in closet with organizers. Two additional bedrooms share a bathroom and are of a generous size. The fourth bedroom's vastness lends itself to multiple uses—be it a bedroom, office, loft, or even a fitness room.  Yet perhaps the jewel in this home's crown is the screened porch. It's the perfect spot for savoring your morning brew, hosting dinners, or simply extending your entertainment space. The community further enhances living here with amenities like the playground, pool, and community events. Plus, its strategic location places shopping and entertainment venues just a stone's throw away. Welcome to your dream home!
